  <section>
    <title>Notifying the SEC</title>
    <section>
      <title>Statewide Events</title>
      <para>
	For statewide events, the SEC is notified by the Michigan State
	Police via E-Team notification when the SEOC is fully activated,
	or a need for amateur radio is perceived.
      </para>
<!--
      <important>
	<title>Keep eTeam up to date</title>
	<para>
	  The SEC monitors E-Team and uses it to update State
	  officials during an incident.  Be sure to keep your SitRep
	  up to date.
	</para>
      </important>
-->
      <para>
	The SEC also monitors E-Team to be alert to incidents which
	may deteriorate to the point that SEC attention is required.
      </para>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Local/Regional events</title>
      <para>
	For local or regional events, the affected EC should notify
	the DEC who will then notify the SEC by E-Team alert or by cell
	phone (989-430-4855).  If the DEC is not available, the EC
	should notify the SEC directly.  For events of lower urgency
	the EC or DEC may prefer email.
	<note>
	  <title>E-Team Alert is best</title>
	  <para>
	    Since E-Team uses multiple paths, the best method of alert
	    is through an E-Team targeted alert.
	  </para>
	</note>
      </para>
      <para>
	Even when a callout does not seem significant, the SEC should
	be notified.  The SEC's broader view may allow him to alert
	ECs to issues not visible to the EC.
      <warning>
	<title>Keep eTeam up to date</title>
	<para>
	  The SEC monitors E-Team and uses it to update State
	  officials during an incident.  Be sure to keep your SitRep
	  up to date.
	</para>
      </warning>
      </para>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>SEOC Station Activation</title>
      <para>
	When the SEOC is fully activated, the Michigan State Police
	notifies the station manager by pager.  For other events, the
	SEC may notify the station manager by telephone as required.
      </para>
    </section>
